<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> The village of Andaluz (41°31', -2°49') lies at the foot of Andaluz Mountain on the Duero River in the province of Soria, and within 10 km of it are the villages of Torreandaluz and Centenera de Andaluz. A brook named Andaluz is said to flow in the province of Guadalajara out of the <a href="http://www.andaduras.com/at_milagros.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.andaduras.com/at_milagros.htm" rel="nofollow">Cueva de la Hoz</a> (41°00', -2°18'). Bossong[online]:10-11, but the coordinates given are according to Google Maps and differ slightly from those in Bossong.</li>
